The paper deals with boosting ensembles, which is a popular machine learning technique for classification and regression tasks. The focus of the paper is on improving the calibration of probability estimates generated by online boosting ensembles. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions cost-sensitive classification, which falls under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and computer vision, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
